# Target classes
#
# A target class bundles the controllers (and, for some classes, the platform /
# ROMFS / drivers) that define a build's "shape". A board's <class>.px4board
# overlay sets CONFIG_TARGET_CLASS_<X>=y; the membership is expressed on each
# member symbol as `default y if TARGET_CLASS_<X>`.
#
# Why `default y if` and not `select`/`imply`:
#  - `select` would force a controller on with no way for a board to drop it, but
#    16 vtol and 8 copter boards legitimately disable an individual controller.
#  - `imply` is silently reverted back ON by Tools/kconfig/merge_config.py's
#    _revert_unset_symbols: it clears a board's `# CONFIG_X is not set`, and only
#    re-pins X off when a y-valued *default* condition exists. A controller's only
#    default is `default n`, so the imply re-fires and the board's disable is lost.
#  - `default y if TARGET_CLASS_<X>` provides exactly that y-valued default, so a
#    board's `# CONFIG_MODULES_X is not set` overlay line wins. Overridable, and
#    the class membership is visible in one place (the member symbol's Kconfig).

menu "Target classes"

